module TS_PRELUDE.

> EUF rule heads for ts2pant's stringification prelude. Pantagruel
> intentionally does not provide an implicit-coercion `to-string`
> primitive: explicit-coercion-only is part of the language design.
> ts2pant therefore imports this module from any consumer spec whose
> TypeScript source contains a stringification site (template literal
> with non-string substitutions, `String(x)` cast, `+`-concat with a
> non-string operand). The dispatch is managed entirely by ts2pant;
> Pantagruel itself is unaware of TS_PRELUDE.
>
> Reference: Kroening & Strichman, *Decision Procedures* Ch. 4
> (Equality with Uninterpreted Functions; congruence is the only
> built-in axiom for opaque calls).
>
> Naming: distinct rule names per source type rather than arity-
> overloaded `to-string` because Pantagruel rules can be arity-
> overloaded but not type-overloaded at the same arity.
>
> Bool stringification is intentionally absent. Pantagruel warns on
> Bool parameters (Bool params on rules are usually a code smell —
> use a predicate, a two-element domain, or split). ts2pant should
> lower `String(b)` / `${b}` for `b: boolean` inline as
> `cond b => "true", true => "false"` rather than route through an
> EUF rule.

int-to-string n: Int => String.
real-to-string r: Real => String.

---
